      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ATTACHMENT (6) came from this barrier last week and while beaten as favourite he missed by only a head. Had won three of his previous four so is in good order. Can atone. IM THE FALCON NZ (3) has had seven weeks off since placing at this venue but has been kept ticking over with a trial. He is good enough to threaten from a favourable draw. TIMS A TROOPER (9) draws on the back row but was brave in toughing it out after racing parked last start, the second time he has won in his last three attempts at this distance. MANILA PLAYBOY (8) has been good from wide barriers of late, winning two back and missing TIMS A TROOPER by a nose last start. Draws for a trail so could be dangerous. DASHING (7) has won a trial since he raced parked and faded last start. Draws out but won four in a row prior so is worth another chance.",
